<TEXT>&#2;<DATELINE>2016-08-31</DATELINE><TITLE>Complementing T-cell Function: An Inhibitory Role of the Complement System in T-cell-Mediated Antitumor Immunity.</TITLE><BODY>New data from Wang and colleagues show that complement C3 suppresses the function of CD8+ tumor-infiltrating T cells by inhibiting IL10 production, and targeting the complement receptors C3aR and C5aR enhances the antitumor activity of immune checkpoint blockade. Their results not only define a new role of complement receptors as T-cell coinhibitory receptors, but also are useful in the development of novel strategies to improve the effectiveness of cancer immunotherapy.&#3;</BODY></TEXT>